I was in there two weeks ago and ordered just a cheese quesadilla. After I placed my order and paid for my dinner, I decided to use the restroom while my food was being prepared. I said yes and reached to grab the bag and he looks over to the girl at the resister and asked her if I paid? I told him that yes I did pay! And he said he was just confirming. He saw me at the register paying for my food and why would he ask her that.? I left in disgust. I wanted  to cuss him out, but I just decided to leave in peace and not create a scene. I have with pleasure visited at least 9 Chipotles markets: Minneapolis' Uptown, MN; Champaign's University; and Casa Grande, AZ has offered the most exemplary service, while Chicago's Hyde Park; Bloomington Main, IL and now this one...could use some lessons in serving. Granted, I am not the typical customer. I generally request seared chicken when its cooked on the grill. Most of the locations have honored that, as expected. I guess I am the only customer to ask for it. However, at this location, serving my bowl seems insurmountable when it came to adding the sides. I usually have the chicken, extra chicken on the bottom. I ask almost every location I visit to stir up the white rice because most of the time, it is clumped together. At this location, when stirring the rice, it was to the bottom of the steam dried container it was in. So, I requested some fresh rice. It took nearly 7 minutes for someone to become available to make the rice and then to complete my bowl. Other customers were willing to accept the bottom of the pan for the rice. I felt frustrated to think I would have gotten faster service if I had done the same. Part of my enjoyment is the preparation of my burrito bowl. When it is thrown together in the name of speed, the presentation is compromised thus affect the enjoyment of my bowl. I generally order it with meat, then black beans dry, corn dry and tomato dry. But, to be so quick to throw cheese on it ( I am allergic to milk) would mean one would have to make it over. I am not criticizing the chain, but this location could take a lesson or two in active listening when it comes to the customers. If I am in Iowa City, I will hesitate before visiting here.
